  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pilot supporting young street-connected mothers to improve outcomes through quality ECD in Accra</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A recent census found there are more than 30,000 young girls living and working on the streets of Accra, the capital of Ghana. Many have small children to support, and to survive they carry heavy loads, sell cheap goods, or engage in sex work. These young mothers may have limited experience of good parenting, so this project works to improve their skills to support their children&apos;s development, improve their financial literacy, and offer quality early years teaching to their children.</narrative>
  </description>
